            's; that there the prisoner gave the pawnbroker's duplicate to the prosecutrix, and said he was sorry for what he had done.</p>
               <p>The prisoner, in his defence, said, that the prosecutrix picked him up; that he carried her to his comrade's room; that there she said she had been married to him five years, and gave him her cloak to pawn.</p>
               <p>He called two soldiers and a woman to prove this, but they gave contradictory accounts of the matter; he also called the man, at whose house he lay, and his serjeant, who gave him a good character.</p>
